Cauliflower with Mushroom Sauce

Pressure Cooker

1 medium to large cauliflower
1 can mushroom soup (says No. 1 can)
1/2 cup milk
1 tsp. salt
1/8 tsp. pepper

Method: Wash cauliflower, drain well, separate into flowerettes and
score stems. Place mushroom soup in cooker. Mix well. Add milk, salt
and pepper. Add cauliflower and spoon sauce over the flowerettes. Place
cover on cooker. Allow steam to flow from vent pipe to release all air
from cooker. Place indicator weight on vent pipe and cook 2 minutes with
stem at COOK position. Cool cooker at once.